    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-13T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-13T12:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.011/8–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_MRD1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-13T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 13, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2033. Preparatory Constitutional Committee appointed by 11 Ministers President
                    and including <persName corresp="#p_SO2">Suhr</persName> from Berlin has met
                    this week at Herrenchiemsee, Bavaria.<note n="1" xml:id="d273fn1">The
                        Preparatory Constitutional Committee (or Committee of Experts) met at
                        Herrenchiemsee from August 10 to August 23. Regarding the transactions of
                        the conference and the report submitted to the Ministers President, see the
                        editorial note, <ref target="#pg_418">p. 418</ref>.</note> Sessions will
                    continue next week. Only scattered indications yet available as to course of
                    committee’s thinking. Military Government maintaining hands-off attitude.
                    Responsible authorities here feel importance of committee’s work should not be
                    overemphasized. <gloss target="#t_SPD1">SPD</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CDU1"
                        >CDU</gloss> and others will likewise have draft constitutions ready for
                    consideration by Parliamentary Council. Civil administration division, <gloss
                        target="#t_OMGUS1">OMGUS</gloss>, believes Ministers President committee <pb
                        facs="0449" n="415" xml:id="pg_415"/> draft will not have as much influence
                    as <gloss target="#t_CDU1">CDU</gloss> draft, since <gloss target="#t_CDU1"
                        >CDU</gloss> will have largest single representation in Council meeting.</p>
                <p>Ministers President are reported favoring Bonn as Parliamentary Council site with
                        <persName>Karlsruhe</persName> runner-up.</p>
                <p>Repeated London as 473.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
